doctype html
html(lang='en')
  head
    meta(charset='utf-8')
    meta(name='viewport', content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no')
    meta(name='description', content='Frequently asked questions about Purple Vector Operations, including service scope, privacy-aware handling, Xestro support, digitisation, retainers, and clinic fit.')
    meta(name='author', content='Purple Vector Operations')
    title FAQ | Purple Vector Operations
    link(rel='icon', type='image/x-icon', href='assets/favicon.ico')
    script(src='https://use.fontawesome.com/releases/v6.3.0/js/all.js', crossorigin='anonymous')
    link(href='https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Montserrat:400,700', rel='stylesheet', type='text/css')
    link(href='https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto+Slab:400,100,300,700', rel='stylesheet', type='text/css')
    link(href='css/styles.css', rel='stylesheet')

  body#page-top
    nav#mainNav.navbar.navbar-expand-lg.navbar-dark.fixed-top
      .container
        a.navbar-brand(href='index.html')
          img(src='assets/img/navbar-logo.svg', alt='Purple Vector Operations')
        button.navbar-toggler(type='button', data-bs-toggle='collapse', data-bs-target='#navbarResponsive', aria-controls='navbarResponsive', aria-expanded='false', aria-label='Toggle navigation')
          | Menu
          i.fas.fa-bars.ms-1
        #navbarResponsive.collapse.navbar-collapse
          ul.navbar-nav.text-uppercase.ms-auto.py-4.py-lg-0
            li.nav-item
              a.nav-link(href='index.html') Home
            li.nav-item
              a.nav-link(href='about.html') About
            li.nav-item
              a.nav-link(href='services.html') Services
            li.nav-item
              a.nav-link(href='process.html') Process
            li.nav-item
              a.nav-link.active(href='faq.html') FAQ
            li.nav-item
              a.nav-link(href='index.html#contact') Contact

    header.masthead(style='padding-top: 12rem; padding-bottom: 6rem;')
      .container
        .masthead-subheading Frequently Asked Questions
        .masthead-heading.text-uppercase The obvious questions clinics ask first
        p.text-white-50.mx-auto(style='max-width: 760px;')
          | Fair enough. No one wants to buy vague support from a mysterious website and hope for the best.

    section.page-section
      .container
        .row.g-4
          .col-lg-6
            .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
              .card-body.p-4
                h4.text-uppercase Does PVO provide clinical advice?
                p.text-muted No. PVO is strictly non-clinical and does not provide diagnosis, treatment, clinical judgment, triage, or medico-legal advice.
          .col-lg-6
            .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
              .card-body.p-4
                h4.text-uppercase What kinds of clinics are a good fit?
                p.text-muted Specialist private practices, individual clinicians, rooms with workflow or admin issues, clinics using Xestro, and practices dealing with legacy paper record backlogs.
          .col-lg-6
            .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
              .card-body.p-4
                h4.text-uppercase Do you replace our existing IT provider?
                p.text-muted No. PVO works alongside existing IT providers where needed. The role is practical operational support, not pretending to absorb every backend system responsibility on earth.
          .col-lg-6
            .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
              .card-body.p-4
                h4.text-uppercase Can you help with Xestro?
                p.text-muted Yes. Support can include setup help, workflow optimisation, template support, historical records access support, and practical troubleshooting around day-to-day clinic use.
          .col-lg-6
            .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
              .card-body.p-4
                h4.text-uppercase Can you scan paper records into digital files?
                p.text-muted Yes. PVO can handle structured paper-to-digital conversion with OCR, file naming, folder organisation, optional upload support, and secure return methods.
          .col-lg-6
            .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
              .card-body.p-4
                h4.text-uppercase How is sensitive information handled?
                p.text-muted Workflows are designed around data minimisation, secure handling, strong access controls, encryption, and privacy-aware operational processes with human review.
          .col-lg-6
            .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
              .card-body.p-4
                h4.text-uppercase Do you use AI tools?
                p.text-muted Where appropriate, internal administrative AI-assisted tools may be used for sorting, classification, and workflow support, with minimisation and human review built into the process.
          .col-lg-6
            .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
              .card-body.p-4
                h4.text-uppercase How are services priced?
                p.text-muted Support can be structured as retainers, one-off projects, digitisation programs, and add-on services depending on scope, workload, and the clinic's environment.

    section.page-section.bg-light
      .container
        .row.justify-content-center
          .col-lg-10
            .text-center.mb-4
              h2.section-heading.text-uppercase Common starting points
              h3.section-subheading.text-muted Most clinics do not begin with a grand transformation plan.
            .row.g-4
              .col-md-4
                .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
                  .card-body.p-4.text-center
                    h4.text-uppercase One messy system
                    p.text-muted A workflow, software issue, or admin bottleneck that staff are sick of working around.
              .col-md-4
                .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
                  .card-body.p-4.text-center
                    h4.text-uppercase One backlog
                    p.text-muted Paper records, inbox overflow, document cleanup, or old tasks that never quite died.
              .col-md-4
                .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
                  .card-body.p-4.text-center
                    h4.text-uppercase One trusted support contact
                    p.text-muted A clinic wants someone who understands both the operational reality and the technical side without making everything harder.

    section.page-section
      .container
        .row.justify-content-center.text-center
          .col-lg-8
            h2.section-heading.text-uppercase Still deciding?
            p.text-muted.mb-4 A short conversation is usually enough to work out whether PVO is a good fit, whether the task should be a project or retainer, and what should definitely stay out of scope.
            a.btn.btn-primary.btn-xl.text-uppercase.me-3(href='services.html') View Services
            a.btn.btn-dark.btn-xl.text-uppercase(href='index.html#contact') Contact PVO

    footer.footer.py-4
      .container
        .row.align-items-center
          .col-lg-4.text-lg-start Copyright © Purple Vector Operations 2026
          .col-lg-4.my-3.my-lg-0
            a.btn.btn-dark.btn-social.mx-2(href='mailto:admin@purplevectoroperations.com', aria-label='Email Purple Vector Operations')
              i.fas.fa-envelope
          .col-lg-4.text-lg-end
            a.link-dark.text-decoration-none.me-3(href='about.html') About
            a.link-dark.text-decoration-none.me-3(href='services.html') Services
            a.link-dark.text-decoration-none.me-3(href='process.html') Process
            a.link-dark.text-decoration-none(href='faq.html') FAQ

    script(src='https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.2.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js')
    script(src='js/scripts.js')
